snippet: The notable absence of some of chess’s elite players may have helped Ukraine grab the title at this year’s Women’s World Team Championship.
abstract: Dylan Loeb McClain Chess column observes that absence of some of chess world’s elite players may have helped Ukraine grab title at 2013 Women’s World Team Championship.
lead_paragraph: The notable absence of some of chess’s elite players may have helped Ukraine grab the title at this year’s Women’s World Team Championship.
